# Build context for the production images (ADR-024). Everything the build
# needs is source + lockfile: the images install and compile from scratch.

# Dependencies and build outputs: reinstalled/rebuilt inside the image, and
# host artifacts would be the wrong platform (native binaries) anyway.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Secrets — never in a build context: an image layer is not a secret store,
# and anyone who can pull the image can read it (ADR-024 §5).
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Runtime data of the dev Lightning fixture: LND macaroons, wallet and channel
# databases (infra/docker/ is development only, never deployed).
infra/docker/volumes

# Locally stored photo blobs (PHOTO_STORAGE_DIR default, ADR-020): user data,
# and in production a volume — never baked into an image.
**/data

# Repo and tooling noise.
.git
.github
.claude
**/*.log
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
